{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Repair Leaflet Map Tile Rendering Issues\n\nFix the broken Leaflet map display where map tiles are rendering incorrectly or appearing corrupted.\n\nRequirements:\n- Diagnose the root cause of tile misalignment or display errors (common causes include container sizing issues, missing CSS, incorrect tile layer configuration, or coordinate system problems)\n- Verify Leaflet library and tile provider URLs are correctly configured\n- Ensure map container has explicit height/width set in CSS (Leaflet requires defined dimensions)\n- Check for map.invalidateSize() calls needed after dynamic container resizing\n- Validate tile layer attribution and source URLs are accessible\n- Test tile loading across different zoom levels and map coordinates\n- Verify z-index and CSS properties aren't conflicting with tile rendering\n- Ensure map initialization occurs after DOM is fully loaded\n- Test in multiple browsers to rule out browser-specific rendering issues\n- Confirm no console errors related to tile loading or CORS issues",
